  "event_preview": "Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya is a 4.657 km (2.894 mi) permanent road course in Montmeló, north of Barcelona. Round 3 of the 2026 FIA Formula 3 Championship takes place June 12-14, supporting the Spanish Grand Prix. The 14-corner layout, used as the traditional pre-season testing venue for Formula One, demands a balance of mechanical grip and aerodynamic efficiency rarely found elsewhere on the calendar.\n\nHeading into Barcelona, Ugo Ugochukwu led the championship after his Melbourne Feature Race victory, with Théophile Naël and Bruno del Pino in close contention. Rafael Câmara, the reigning champion, looked to add to his strong record at this circuit — he won the 2025 Barcelona feature race from pole and set the fastest lap in the same session. Théophile Naël topped pre-season testing at Barcelona in February, suggesting his Van Amersfoort Racing machinery would again be competitive at the Catalan circuit.\n\nThe all-time FIA Formula 3 qualifying record at Barcelona belongs to Rafael Câmara, who set a 1:28.761 to claim pole for the 2025 feature race. The race lap record is also Câmara's, a 1:31.350 set during that same race.",
